<subSubSection id="C3216515FFEAFF882EF6FD3CF8E3C123" pageId="0" pageNumber="234" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B84369EFFEAFF882EF6FD3CF7DDC75B" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">• Mediumto large-sized mammals with round or pointed ears relatively large in comparison to body size, exceptionally powerfuljaw muscles, hindquarters long and sloping; somewhat dog-like in overall appearance, very muscular.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF446616FFEAFF882EF6FCE6FA2BC773" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6350104" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6350104" box="[1260,1469,862,888]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6350104/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="234" startId="0.[1260,1274,867,882]" targetBox="[1522,1853,881,1104]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph id="8B84369EFFEAFF882EF6FCE6FA2BC773" blockId="0.[1260,1469,862,888]" box="[1260,1469,862,888]" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">• 85-185 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF446616FFEAFF882EF7FBEFF960C080" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6350106" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6350106" box="[1261,1782,1130,1163]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6350106/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="234" targetBox="[243,1185,703,1326]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph id="8B84369EFFEAFF882EF7FBEFF960C080" box="[1261,1782,1130,1163]" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">
• Africa and Middle East to 
<collectingCountry id="F32C760EFFEAFF882CBAFBEFF964C080" box="[1696,1778,1130,1163]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B84369EFFEAFF882EF7FB14F7DAC0D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">• Mainly savannas, but other semi-arid and desert regions to edges of forests, both tropical and temperate zones.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B84369EFFEAFF882EF4FB5AF8EAC10B" box="[1262,1916,1247,1280]" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">
• 
<figureCitation id="13002A1BFFEAFF882F09FB5AF8EEC10B" box="[1299,1912,1247,1280]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="0.[2251,2322,1447,1468]" captionTargetBox="[1227,2174,1463,1739]" captionTargetPageId="0" captionText="Figure 1: Phylogenyof the extant Hyaenidae. Relationships &amp; divergence times (mya=mullion years ago) from Koepfli et al. (2006)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6554220/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">4 genera, 4 species, at least 5 extant taxa</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B84369EFFEAFF882EF4FA8EF8E3C123" box="[1262,1909,1291,1320]" pageId="0" pageNumber="234">• All Lower Risk; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
